"script": "When someone collapses and a defibrillator screams clear, you'd think the shock restarts a stopped heart. But it does the exact opposite. You see, in a real cardiac arrest the heart isn't stopped, it's quivering chaotically, every muscle cell firing out of sync, so no blood gets pumped. The defibrillator slams a massive jolt of electricity through all of those cells at once. And this forces every single one to stop and reset at the same instant. Then, in that silence, the heart's natural pacemaker takes over and fires a clean beat. So we shock a heart to death to bring it back to life.",
